    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-29T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-29T08:00:00-05:00" n="328"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d328">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">870.811/235: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-29T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 29, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:17 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1637. My 4477, October 27, 1 p.m. 1940.<note n="76" xml:id="d328fn76">Not
                        printed, but see telegram No. 670, October 26, 1940, from the Minister in
                        Rumania, <ref target="frus1940v01#pg_524">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1940, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 524</ref>.</note> It is announced in
                    Berlin that the seat of the International Danube Commission has been moved from
                    Belgrade to Orsova, the “Serbian” representative and administrative personnel
                    have been excluded from the Commission, the transit fees at the Iron Gate are in
                    future payable in marks rather than Swiss francs and German has been designated
                    the “official language in the administration of the Iron Gate”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
